{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Right when I was 15 was when\nI first got interested in solar energy."},{"time":3719,"text":"My family had moved from Fort Lee,\nNew Jersey to California,"},{"time":6600,"text":"from the snow to lots of heat,\nand gas lines."},{"time":8960,"text":"There was gas rationing in 1973."},{"time":11360,"text":"The energy crisis was in full bore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":13440,"text":"I started reading\n\"Popular Science\" magazine,"},{"time":15600,"text":"and I got really excited\nabout the potential of solar energy"},{"time":18480,"text":"to try and solve that crisis."},{"time":20240,"text":"I had just taken\ntrigonometry in high school,"},{"time":22400,"text":"I learned about the parabola"},{"time":23800,"text":"and how it could concentrate\nrays of light to a single focus."},{"time":26720,"text":"That got me very excited."},{"time":28320,"text":"And I really felt\nthat there would be potential"},{"time":30560,"text":"to build some kind of thing\nthat could concentrate light."},{"time":33280,"text":"So, I started this company\ncalled Solar Devices."},{"time":36000,"text":"And this was a company\nwhere I built parabolas,"},{"time":38280,"text":"I took metal shop,"},{"time":39560,"text":"and I remember walking into metal shop\nbuilding parabolas and Stirling engines."},{"time":43320,"text":"And I was building a Stirling engine\nover on the lathe,"},{"time":45960,"text":"and all the motorcycle guys said,\n\"You're building a bong, aren't you?\""},{"time":49320,"text":"And I said, \"No, it's a Stirling engine.\"\nBut they didn't believe me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52600,"text":"I sold the plans for this engine"},{"time":54680,"text":"and for this dish in the back\nof \"Popular Science\" magazine,"},{"time":57560,"text":"for four dollars each."},{"time":59000,"text":"And I earned enough money\nto pay for my first year of Caltech."},{"time":61960,"text":"It was a really big excitement for me\nto get into Caltech."},{"time":64720,"text":"And at my first year at Caltech,\nI continued the business."},{"time":67800,"text":"But then, in the second year of Caltech,\nthey started grading."},{"time":70760,"text":"The whole first year was pass/fail,\nbut the second year was graded."},{"time":73960,"text":"I wasn't able to keep up\nwith the business,"},{"time":76040,"text":"and I ended up with a 25-year detour."},{"time":77880,"text":"My dream had been to convert solar energy\nat a very practical cost,"},{"time":81080,"text":"but then I had this big detour."},{"time":82640,"text":"First, the coursework at Caltech."},{"time":84280,"text":"Then, when I graduated from Caltech,\nthe IBM PC came out,"},{"time":87040,"text":"and I got addicted to the IBM PC in 1981."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89120,"text":"And then in 1983, Lotus 1-2-3 came out,"},{"time":91480,"text":"and I was completely blown away\nby Lotus 1-2-3."},{"time":93720,"text":"I began operating my business with 1-2-3,\nbegan writing add-ins for 1-2-3,"},{"time":97920,"text":"wrote a natural language\ninterface to 1-2-3."},{"time":100280,"text":"I started an educational software company\nafter I joined Lotus,"},{"time":103280,"text":"and then I started Idealab\nso I could have a roof"},{"time":105640,"text":"under which I could build\nmultiple companies in succession."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108800,"text":"Much later -- in 2000, very recently --\nthe new California energy crisis --"},{"time":113204,"text":"what was purported to be\na big energy crisis -- was coming."},{"time":116059,"text":"And I was trying to figure out"},{"time":117540,"text":"if we could build something\nthat would capitalize on that"},{"time":120261,"text":"and get people backup energy,\nin case the crisis really came."},{"time":123170,"text":"And I started looking at how\nwe could build battery backup systems"},{"time":126305,"text":"that could give people five hours,\n10 hours, maybe even a full day,"},{"time":129500,"text":"or three days' worth of backup power."},{"time":131440,"text":"I'm glad you heard earlier today,\nbatteries are unbelievably --"},{"time":134480,"text":"lack density compared to fuel."},{"time":137480,"text":"So much more energy can be stored\nwith fuel than with batteries."},{"time":140520,"text":"You'd have to fill your entire\nparking space of one garage space"},{"time":143600,"text":"just to give yourself\nfour hours of battery backup."},{"time":146040,"text":"And I concluded, after researching\nevery other technology"},{"time":148760,"text":"that we could deploy for storing energy --"},{"time":150800,"text":"flywheels, different\nformulations of batteries --"},{"time":153160,"text":"it just wasn't practical to store energy."},{"time":155560,"text":"So what about making energy?\nMaybe we could make energy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158240,"text":"I tried to figure out --\nmaybe solar's become attractive."},{"time":160960,"text":"It's been 25 years since I was doing this,"},{"time":163040,"text":"let me go back and look\nat what's been happening with solar cells."},{"time":166200,"text":"And the price had gone down\nfrom 10 dollars a watt"},{"time":168600,"text":"to about four or five dollars a watt,\nbut it stabilized."},{"time":171280,"text":"And it needed to get much lower\nto be cost-effective."},{"time":173800,"text":"I studied all the new things\nthat had happened in solar cells,"},{"time":176729,"text":"and was looking for ways we could\nmake solar cells more inexpensively."},{"time":180120,"text":"A lot of new things\nare happening to do that,"},{"time":182520,"text":"but fundamentally, the process\nrequires a tremendous amount of energy."},{"time":185880,"text":"Some people say it takes\nmore energy to make a solar cell"},{"time":188600,"text":"than it will give out in its entire life."},{"time":190600,"text":"If we reduce the amount of energy\nit takes to make the cells,"},{"time":193520,"text":"that will become more practical."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195120,"text":"But right now, you pretty much\nhave to take silicon,"},{"time":197600,"text":"put it in an oven at 1600 F\nfor 17 hours, to make the cells."},{"time":201200,"text":"A lot of people are working\nto try and reduce that,"},{"time":203640,"text":"but I didn't have anything to contribute."},{"time":205640,"text":"So I tried to figure out\nwhat other way could we try"},{"time":208120,"text":"to make cost-effective solar electricity."},{"time":210320,"text":"What if we collect the sun\nwith a large reflector --"},{"time":212800,"text":"like I had been thinking about\nin high school,"},{"time":215000,"text":"but maybe with modern technology\nwe could make it cheaper --"},{"time":217840,"text":"concentrate it to a small converter,"},{"time":219920,"text":"and then the conversion device\nwouldn't have to be as expensive,"},{"time":223000,"text":"because it's much smaller,\nrather than solar cells,"},{"time":225480,"text":"which have to cover the entire surface\nthat you want to gather sun from."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228920,"text":"This seemed practical now,"},{"time":230200,"text":"because a lot of new technologies\nhad come in the 25 years"},{"time":232960,"text":"since I had last looked at it."},{"time":234440,"text":"There was a lot\nof new manufacturing techniques,"},{"time":236720,"text":"not to mention really cheap\nminiature motors --"},{"time":238960,"text":"brushless motors,\nservomotors, stepper motors,"},{"time":241160,"text":"that are used in printers and scanners."},{"time":243080,"text":"So, that's a breakthrough."},{"time":244360,"text":"Of course, inexpensive microprocessors"},{"time":246240,"text":"and a very important breakthrough --\ngenetic algorithms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249160,"text":"I'll be very short on genetic algorithms."},{"time":251160,"text":"It's a powerful way of solving intractable\nproblems using natural selection."},{"time":254760,"text":"You take a problem that you can't solve\nwith a pure mathematical answer,"},{"time":258200,"text":"you build an evolutionary system\nto try multiple tries at guessing,"},{"time":261399,"text":"you add sex --"},{"time":262640,"text":"where you take half of one solution\nand half of another"},{"time":265280,"text":"and then make new mutations --"},{"time":266760,"text":"and you use natural selection\nto kill off not-as-good solutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269840,"text":"Usually, with a genetic algorithm\non a computer today,"},{"time":272440,"text":"with a three gigahertz processor,"},{"time":274200,"text":"you can solve many\nformerly intractable problems"},{"time":276953,"text":"in just a matter of minutes."},{"time":278480,"text":"So we tried to come up with a way\nto use genetic algorithms"},{"time":281560,"text":"to create a new type of concentrator."},{"time":283400,"text":"And I'll show you what we came up with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285320,"text":"Traditionally,\nconcentrators look like this."},{"time":287440,"text":"Those shapes are parabolas."},{"time":288800,"text":"They take all the parallel incoming rays\nand focus it to a single spot."},{"time":292200,"text":"They have to track the sun,"},{"time":293520,"text":"because they have to point\ndirectly at the sun."},{"time":295760,"text":"They usually have\na one degree acceptance angle --"},{"time":298160,"text":"once they're more than a degree off,"},{"time":299920,"text":"none of the sunlight rays\nwill hit the focus."},{"time":302080,"text":"So we tried to come up\nwith a non-tracking collector"},{"time":304560,"text":"that would gather much more than\none degree of light, with no moving parts."},{"time":308120,"text":"So we created a genetic algorithm\nto try this out,"},{"time":310520,"text":"we made a model in Excel\nof a multisurface reflector,"},{"time":313120,"text":"and an amazing thing evolved, literally,"},{"time":315200,"text":"from trying a billion cycles,\na billion different attempts,"},{"time":318040,"text":"with a fitness function that defined\nhow can you collect the most light,"},{"time":321480,"text":"from the most angles,\nover a day, from the sun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323720,"text":"And this is the shape that evolved."},{"time":325440,"text":"It's this non-tracking collector\nwith these six tuba-like horns,"},{"time":329120,"text":"and each of them collect light\nin the following way --"},{"time":331680,"text":"if the sunlight strikes right here,"},{"time":333400,"text":"it might bounce right to the center,\nthe hot spot, directly,"},{"time":336280,"text":"but if the sun is off axis\nand comes from the side,"},{"time":338720,"text":"it might hit two places\nand take two bounces."},{"time":341160,"text":"So for direct light,\nit takes only one bounce,"},{"time":344000,"text":"for off-axis light it might take two,"},{"time":345920,"text":"and for extreme off-axis,\nit might take three."},{"time":348440,"text":"Your efficiency goes down\nwith more bounces,"},{"time":350560,"text":"because you lose about 10 percent\nwith each bounce,"},{"time":353000,"text":"but this allowed us to collect light\nfrom a plus or minus 25-degree angle."},{"time":356880,"text":"So, about two and a half hours of the day"},{"time":359080,"text":"we could collect\nwith a stationary component."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361440,"text":"Solar cells collect light\nfor four and a half hours though."},{"time":364240,"text":"On an average adjusted day,\na solar cell --"},{"time":366520,"text":"because the sun's moving across the sky,"},{"time":368480,"text":"the solar cell is going down\nwith a sine wave function of performance"},{"time":371760,"text":"at the off-axis angles."},{"time":373040,"text":"It collects about four and a half\naverage hours of sunlight a day."},{"time":376200,"text":"So even this, although it was great\nwith no moving parts --"},{"time":379000,"text":"we could achieve high\ntemperatures -- wasn't enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381480,"text":"We needed to beat solar cells."},{"time":382960,"text":"So we took a look at another idea."},{"time":384640,"text":"We looked at a way to break up a parabola\ninto individual petals that would track."},{"time":388522,"text":"So what you see here is 12 separate petals"},{"time":390920,"text":"that each could be controlled\nwith individual microprocessors"},{"time":393840,"text":"that would only cost a dollar."},{"time":395320,"text":"You can buy a two-megahertz\nmicroprocessor for a dollar now."},{"time":398360,"text":"And you can buy stepper motors\nthat pretty much never wear out"},{"time":401560,"text":"because they have no brushes,"},{"time":403200,"text":"for a dollar."},{"time":404440,"text":"So we can control all 12 of these petals\nfor under 50 dollars"},{"time":408120,"text":"and what this would allow us to do\nis not have to move the focus any more,"},{"time":411640,"text":"but only move the petals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412920,"text":"The whole system would have\na much lower profile,"},{"time":415280,"text":"but also we could gather sunlight\nfor six and a half to seven hours a day."},{"time":418800,"text":"Now that we have concentrated sunlight,"},{"time":420720,"text":"what are we going to put at the center\nto convert sunlight to electricity?"},{"time":424240,"text":"So we tried to look\nat all the different heat engines"},{"time":426760,"text":"that have been used in history to convert\nsunlight or heat to electricity,"},{"time":431600,"text":"And one of the great ones of all time,"},{"time":433480,"text":"James Watt's steam engine of 1788\nwas a major breakthrough."},{"time":436680,"text":"James Watt didn't actually invent\nthe steam engine, he just refined it."},{"time":440040,"text":"But his refinements were incredible."},{"time":441800,"text":"He added new linear\nmotion guides to the pistons,"},{"time":444160,"text":"he added a condenser\nto cool the steam outside the cylinder,"},{"time":447040,"text":"he made the engine double-acting,\nso it had double the power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449960,"text":"Those were major breakthroughs.\nAll of the improvements he made --"},{"time":453120,"text":"and it's justifiable\nthat our measure of energy, the watt,"},{"time":456560,"text":"today is named after him."},{"time":458120,"text":"So we looked at this engine,\nand this had some potential."},{"time":460840,"text":"Steam engines are dangerous,"},{"time":462240,"text":"and they had tremendous impact\non the world --"},{"time":464440,"text":"industrial revolution\nand ships and locomotives."},{"time":466720,"text":"But they're usually good to be large,"},{"time":468560,"text":"so they're not good\nfor distributed power generation."},{"time":471080,"text":"They're also very high-pressure,\nso they're dangerous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473640,"text":"Another type of engine\nis the hot air engine."},{"time":476240,"text":"And the hot air engine\nalso was not invented by Robert Stirling,"},{"time":479320,"text":"but Robert Stirling came along in 1816\nand radically improved it."},{"time":482400,"text":"This engine, because it was\nso interesting --"},{"time":484560,"text":"it only worked on air, no steam --"},{"time":486240,"text":"has led to hundreds\nof creative designs over the years"},{"time":489000,"text":"that use the Stirling engine principle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491360,"text":"But after the Stirling engine,\nOtto came along,"},{"time":493600,"text":"and also, he didn't invent\nthe internal combustion engine,"},{"time":496360,"text":"he just refined it."},{"time":497600,"text":"He showed it in Paris in 1867,\nand it was a major achievement"},{"time":500520,"text":"because it brought the power density\nof the engine way up."},{"time":503280,"text":"You could now get a lot more power\nin a lot smaller space,"},{"time":506040,"text":"and that allowed the engine\nto be used for mobile applications."},{"time":509040,"text":"So, once you have mobility,"},{"time":510520,"text":"you're making a lot of engines\nbecause you've got lots of units,"},{"time":513600,"text":"as opposed to steam ships\nor big factories,"},{"time":515624,"text":"so this was the engine that ended up\nbenefiting from mass production"},{"time":518919,"text":"where all the other engines didn't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520640,"text":"So, because it went into mass production,"},{"time":522617,"text":"costs were reduced,\n100 years of refinement,"},{"time":525200,"text":"emissions were reduced,\ntremendous production value."},{"time":528000,"text":"There have been hundreds of millions\nof internal combustion engines built,"},{"time":531520,"text":"compared to thousands\nof Stirling engines built."},{"time":533800,"text":"And not nearly as many\nsmall steam engines being built anymore,"},{"time":536800,"text":"only large ones for big operations."},{"time":538520,"text":"So after looking\nat these three, and 47 others,"},{"time":541200,"text":"we concluded that the Stirling engine\nwould be the best one to use."},{"time":544400,"text":"I want to give you a brief explanation\nof how we looked at it and how it works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548320,"text":"So we tried to look\nat the Stirling engine in a new way,"},{"time":551000,"text":"because it was practical --"},{"time":553560,"text":"weight no longer mattered\nfor our application."},{"time":555840,"text":"The internal combustion engine\ntook off because weight mattered,"},{"time":558960,"text":"because you were moving around."},{"time":560520,"text":"But if you're trying to generate\nsolar energy in a static place"},{"time":563520,"text":"the weight doesn't matter so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":565200,"text":"We also discovered that efficiency\ndoesn't matter so much"},{"time":567899,"text":"if your energy source is free."},{"time":569380,"text":"Normally, efficiency is crucial"},{"time":570901,"text":"because the fuel cost\nof your engine over its life"},{"time":573861,"text":"dwarfs the cost of the engine."},{"time":575560,"text":"But if your fuel source is free,"},{"time":577160,"text":"then the only thing that matters"},{"time":578760,"text":"is the up-front\ncapital cost of the engine."},{"time":580800,"text":"So you don't want\nto optimize for efficiency,"},{"time":582960,"text":"you want to optimize for power per dollar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585000,"text":"So using that new twist,\nwith the new criteria,"},{"time":587240,"text":"we thought we could\nrelook at the Stirling engine,"},{"time":589640,"text":"and also bring genetic algorithms in."},{"time":591480,"text":"Basically, Robert Stirling\ndidn't have Gordon Moore before him"},{"time":594440,"text":"to get us three gigahertz\nof processor power."},{"time":596600,"text":"So we took the same genetic algorithm"},{"time":598421,"text":"that we used earlier\nto make that concentrator,"},{"time":600662,"text":"which didn't work out for us,"},{"time":602138,"text":"to optimize the Stirling engine,"},{"time":603720,"text":"and make its design sizes\nand all of its dimensions"},{"time":606960,"text":"the exact optimum\nto get the most power per dollar,"},{"time":610080,"text":"irrespective of weight,\nirrespective of size,"},{"time":612240,"text":"just to get the most conversion\nof solar energy,"},{"time":614520,"text":"because the sun is free."},{"time":615760,"text":"And that's the process we took --\nlet me show you how the engine works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619120,"text":"The simplest heat engine,\nor hot air engine, of all time"},{"time":621800,"text":"would be this -- take a box,\na steel canister, with a piston."},{"time":625040,"text":"Put a flame under it, the piston moves up."},{"time":627360,"text":"Take it off the flame\nand pour water on it, or let it cool down,"},{"time":630400,"text":"the piston moves down."},{"time":631640,"text":"That's a heat engine."},{"time":632880,"text":"That's the most fundamental\nheat engine you could have."},{"time":635520,"text":"The problem is the efficiency\nis one hundredth of one percent,"},{"time":638600,"text":"because you're heating\nall the metal of the chamber"},{"time":641040,"text":"and then cooling all the metal\nof the chamber each time."},{"time":643720,"text":"And you're only getting power from the air\nthat's heating at the same time,"},{"time":647280,"text":"but you're wasting energy\nheating and cooling the metal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":649960,"text":"So someone came up\nwith a very clever idea."},{"time":652040,"text":"Instead of heating and cooling\nthe whole cylinder,"},{"time":654440,"text":"what about if you put\na displacer inside --"},{"time":656480,"text":"a little thing that shuttles\nthe air back and forth."},{"time":658960,"text":"You move that up and down\nwith a little bit of energy"},{"time":661480,"text":"but now you're only shifting the air down\nto the hot end and up to the cold end."},{"time":665280,"text":"So, now you're not alternately heating\nand cooling the metal, just the air."},{"time":669480,"text":"That allows you to get the efficiency up"},{"time":671440,"text":"from a hundredth of a percent\nto about two percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":673880,"text":"And then Robert Stirling\ncame along with this genius idea,"},{"time":676640,"text":"which was, well, I'm still\nnot heating the metal now,"},{"time":679160,"text":"with this kind of engine,"},{"time":680400,"text":"but I'm still reheating all the air."},{"time":682160,"text":"I'm still heating the air every time\nand cooling the air every time."},{"time":685400,"text":"What about if I put\na thermal sponge in the middle,"},{"time":688040,"text":"in the passageway between where the air\nhas to move between hot and cold?"},{"time":691960,"text":"So he made fine wires, and cracked glass,"},{"time":694640,"text":"and all different kinds of materials\nto be a heat sponge."},{"time":697360,"text":"So when the air pushes up\nto go from the hot end to the cold end,"},{"time":700440,"text":"it puts some heat into the sponge."},{"time":702640,"text":"And then when the air comes back\nafter it's been cooled,"},{"time":705320,"text":"it picks up that heat again."},{"time":706720,"text":"So you're reusing your energy\nfive or six times,"},{"time":709760,"text":"and that brings the efficiency\nup to between 30 and 40 percent."},{"time":712760,"text":"It's a little known, but brilliant,\ngenius invention of Robert Stirling"},{"time":716120,"text":"that takes the hot air engine\nfrom being somewhat impractical --"},{"time":719160,"text":"like I found out when I made\nthe real simple version in high school --"},{"time":722520,"text":"to very potentially possible,"},{"time":723960,"text":"once you get the efficiency up,"},{"time":725520,"text":"if you can design this\nto be low enough cost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":727680,"text":"So we really set out on a path\nto try and make the lowest cost possible."},{"time":731120,"text":"We built a huge mathematical model\nof how a Stirling engine works."},{"time":734280,"text":"We applied the genetic algorithm."},{"time":735920,"text":"We got the results from that\nfor the optimal engine."},{"time":738400,"text":"We built engines --"},{"time":739640,"text":"so we built 100 different engines\nover the last two years."},{"time":742400,"text":"We measured each one, we readjusted\nthe model to what we measured,"},{"time":745560,"text":"and then we led that\nto the current prototype."},{"time":747760,"text":"It led to a very compact,\ninexpensive engine,"},{"time":749920,"text":"and this is what the engine looks like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":751840,"text":"Let me show you\nwhat it looks like in real life."},{"time":755440,"text":"So this is the engine.\nIt's just a small cylinder down here,"},{"time":759160,"text":"which holds the generator\ninside and all the linkage,"},{"time":761880,"text":"and it's the hot cap --\nthe hot cylinder on the top --"},{"time":765240,"text":"this part gets hot, this part is cool,"},{"time":767520,"text":"and electricity comes out."},{"time":769480,"text":"The exact converse is also true."},{"time":771360,"text":"If you put electricity in,\nthis will get hot and this will get cold,"},{"time":774760,"text":"you get refrigeration."},{"time":776080,"text":"So it's a complete reversible cycle,"},{"time":777920,"text":"a very efficient cycle,\nand quite a simple thing to make."},{"time":780920,"text":"So now you put the two things together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":782840,"text":"So you have the engine."},{"time":784080,"text":"What if you combine\nthe petals and the engine in the center?"},{"time":786960,"text":"The petals track and the engine\ngets the concentrated sunlight,"},{"time":789960,"text":"takes that heat\nand turns it into electricity."},{"time":792160,"text":"This is what the first prototype\nof our system looked like"},{"time":794920,"text":"with the petals\nand the engine in the center."},{"time":797080,"text":"This is being run out in the sun,"},{"time":798720,"text":"and now I want to show you\nwhat the actual thing looks like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":807280,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":812640,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":813880,"text":"So this is a unit with the 12 petals."},{"time":816560,"text":"These petals cost about a dollar each --"},{"time":818520,"text":"they're lightweight,\ninjection-molded plastic, aluminized."},{"time":821280,"text":"The mechanism to control\neach petal is below there,"},{"time":823967,"text":"with a microprocessor on each one."},{"time":826040,"text":"There are thermocouples on the engine --"},{"time":828000,"text":"little sensors that detect the heat\nwhen the sunlight strikes them."},{"time":831200,"text":"Each petal adjusts itself separately\nto keep the highest temperature on it."},{"time":835080,"text":"When the sun comes out in the morning,\nthe petals will seek the sun,"},{"time":838320,"text":"find it by searching\nfor the highest temperature."},{"time":840680,"text":"About a minute and a half or two minutes\nafter the rays are striking the hot cap"},{"time":844640,"text":"the engine will be warm enough to start"},{"time":846560,"text":"and then the engine\nwill generate electricity"},{"time":848720,"text":"for about six and a half hours a day --"},{"time":850640,"text":"six and a half to seven hours\nas the sun moves across the sky."}]},{"cues":[{"time":853600,"text":"A critical part\nthat we can take advantage of"},{"time":855760,"text":"is that we have these\ninexpensive microprocessors"},{"time":858120,"text":"and each of these petals is autonomous,"},{"time":860040,"text":"and each of these petals figures out\nwhere the sun is with no user setup."},{"time":863520,"text":"So you don't have to tell\nwhat latitude, longitude you're at,"},{"time":866440,"text":"what your roof slope angle is,\nor what orientation."},{"time":868880,"text":"It doesn't really care."},{"time":870160,"text":"What it does is it searches\nto find the hottest spot,"},{"time":872760,"text":"it searches again a half an hour later,\na day later, a month later."},{"time":876720,"text":"It basically figures out\nwhere on Earth you are"},{"time":878960,"text":"by watching the direction the sun moves,"},{"time":880920,"text":"so you don't have to\nactually enter anything about that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":883600,"text":"The way the unit works is,"},{"time":884920,"text":"when the sun comes out,\nthe engine will start"},{"time":887240,"text":"and you get power out here."},{"time":888800,"text":"We have AC and DC, get 12 volts DC,"},{"time":892520,"text":"so that could be used\nfor certain applications."},{"time":894760,"text":"We have an inverter in there,\nso you get 117 volts AC."},{"time":897360,"text":"And you also get hot water.\nThe hot water's optional."},{"time":899960,"text":"You don't have to use it,\nit will cool itself."},{"time":902240,"text":"But you can use it\nto optionally heat hot water"},{"time":904480,"text":"and that brings\nthe efficiency up even higher"},{"time":906640,"text":"because some of the heat\nthat you'd normally be rejecting,"},{"time":909400,"text":"you can now use as useful energy,\nwhether it's for a pool or hot water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":912800,"text":"Let me show you a quick movie\nof what this looks like running."},{"time":921080,"text":"This is the first test\nwhere we took it outside"},{"time":923320,"text":"and each of the petals\nwere individually seeking."},{"time":925680,"text":"And what they do is step,\nvery coarsely at first,"},{"time":928080,"text":"and very finely afterward."},{"time":929360,"text":"Once they get a temperature reading\non the thermocouple"},{"time":932000,"text":"indicating they found the sun,"},{"time":933480,"text":"they slow down and do a fine search."},{"time":935240,"text":"Then the petals will move into position,\nand the engine will start."}]},{"cues":[{"time":938440,"text":"We've been working on this\nfor the last two years."},{"time":940840,"text":"We're very excited about the progress,\nwe have a long way to go though."},{"time":944240,"text":"This is how we envision\nit would be in a residential installation:"},{"time":947520,"text":"you'd probably have\nmore than one unit on your roof."},{"time":950000,"text":"It could be on your roof,\nyour backyard, or somewhere else."},{"time":952840,"text":"You don't have to have enough units\nto power your entire house,"},{"time":955840,"text":"you just save money\nwith each incremental one you add."}]},{"cues":[{"time":958400,"text":"So you're still using\nthe grid potentially,"},{"time":960520,"text":"in this type of application,\nto be your backup supply --"},{"time":963200,"text":"of course, you can't use these at night,\nand you can't use these on cloudy days."},{"time":967000,"text":"But by reducing your energy use,\npretty much at the peak times --"},{"time":970440,"text":"usually when you have\nyour air conditioning on,"},{"time":972680,"text":"or other times like that --"},{"time":974040,"text":"this generates the peak power\nat the peak usage time,"},{"time":976560,"text":"so it's very complementary in that sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":978560,"text":"This is how we would envision\na residential application."},{"time":981240,"text":"We also think there's\nvery big potential for energy farms,"},{"time":984000,"text":"especially in remote land\nwhere there happens to be a lot of sun."},{"time":987120,"text":"It's a really good combination\nof those two factors."},{"time":989600,"text":"It turns out there's a lot of powerful sun\nall around the world, obviously,"},{"time":993160,"text":"but in special places"},{"time":994440,"text":"where it happens to be\nrelatively inexpensive to place these"},{"time":997320,"text":"and also in many more places\nwhere there is high wind power."},{"time":1000200,"text":"So an example of that is,\nhere's the map of the United States."},{"time":1003600,"text":"Pretty much everywhere that's\nnot green or blue is a really ideal place,"},{"time":1007040,"text":"but even the green or blue areas are good,"},{"time":1009080,"text":"just not as good as the places\nthat are red, orange and yellow."},{"time":1012080,"text":"But the hot spot right around Las Vegas\nand Death Valley is very good."},{"time":1015440,"text":"And is only affects the payback period,"},{"time":1017544,"text":"it doesn't mean that you\ncouldn't use solar energy;"},{"time":1020000,"text":"you could use it anywhere on Earth."},{"time":1021720,"text":"It just affects the payback period"},{"time":1023400,"text":"if you're comparing\nto grid-supplied electricity."},{"time":1025760,"text":"But if you don't have\ngrid-supplied electricity,"},{"time":1028039,"text":"then the question of payback\nis a different one entirely."},{"time":1030760,"text":"It's just how many watts\ndo you get per dollar,"},{"time":1033000,"text":"and how could you benefit from that\nto change your life in some way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1036240,"text":"This is the map of the whole Earth,"},{"time":1038350,"text":"and you can see\na huge swathe in the middle"},{"time":1040431,"text":"where a large part of the population is,"},{"time":1042393,"text":"there's tremendous chances\nfor solar energy."},{"time":1044970,"text":"And of course, look at Africa."},{"time":1046451,"text":"The potential to take advantage\nof solar energy there is unbelievable,"},{"time":1049772,"text":"and I'm really excited to talk more\nabout finding ways we can help with that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1053453,"text":"So, in conclusion, I would say\nmy journey has shown me"},{"time":1057199,"text":"that you can revisit\nold ideas in a new light,"},{"time":1060520,"text":"and sometimes ideas\nthat have been discarded in the past"},{"time":1063240,"text":"can be practical now if you apply\nsome new technology or new twists."},{"time":1066800,"text":"We believe we're getting very close\nto something practical and affordable."},{"time":1070320,"text":"Our short-term goal for this\nis to be half the price of solar cells"},{"time":1073520,"text":"and our longer-term goal\nis to be less than a five-year payback."},{"time":1076600,"text":"And at less than a five-year payback,\nthis becomes very economic."},{"time":1079760,"text":"So you don't have to just have\na feel-good attitude about energy"},{"time":1082840,"text":"to want to have one of these."},{"time":1084280,"text":"It just makes economic sense."},{"time":1085720,"text":"Right now, solar paybacks\nare between 30 and 50 years."},{"time":1088320,"text":"If you get it down below five years,"},{"time":1090080,"text":"then it's almost a no-brainer\nbecause the interest to own it --"},{"time":1093080,"text":"someone else will finance it for you\nand you can just make money from day one."},{"time":1096800,"text":"So that's our real powerful goal"},{"time":1098400,"text":"that we're really\nshooting for in the company."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1100600,"text":"Two other things that I learned\nthat were very surprising to me --"},{"time":1103760,"text":"one was how casual we are about energy."},{"time":1108960,"text":"I was walking from the elevator over here,"},{"time":1111360,"text":"and even just looking\nat the stage right now --"},{"time":1113600,"text":"so there's probably\n20,500-watt lights right now."},{"time":1117160,"text":"There's 10,000 watts of light\npouring on the stage,"},{"time":1119600,"text":"one horsepower\nis 746 watts, at full power."},{"time":1123000,"text":"So there's basically 15 horses running\nat full speed just to keep the stage lit."},{"time":1127760,"text":"Not to mention the 200 horses\nthat are probably running right now"},{"time":1130880,"text":"to keep the air-conditioning going."},{"time":1132600,"text":"And it's just amazing,"},{"time":1133840,"text":"walk in the elevator,\nand there's lights on in the elevator."},{"time":1136720,"text":"Of course, now I'm very sensitive at home\nwhen we leave the lights on by mistake."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1140560,"text":"But, everywhere around us\nwe have insatiable use for energy"},{"time":1143400,"text":"because it's so cheap."},{"time":1144680,"text":"And it's cheap because\nwe've been subsidized by energy"},{"time":1147240,"text":"that's been concentrated by the sun."},{"time":1149000,"text":"Basically, oil is\nsolar-energy concentrate."},{"time":1151880,"text":"It's been pounded for a billion years\nwith a lot of energy"},{"time":1155240,"text":"to make it have all that energy\ncontained in it."},{"time":1157520,"text":"And we don't have a birthright"},{"time":1159000,"text":"to just use that up\nas fast as we are, I think."},{"time":1161240,"text":"And it would be great if we could\nmake our energy usage renewable,"},{"time":1164440,"text":"where as we're using the energy,\nwe're creating it at the same pace,"},{"time":1167680,"text":"and I really hope we can get there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1169400,"text":"Thank you very much,\nyou've been a great audience."}]}]}